features: Healthier cooking in 30 min or less: Thanks to rapid air technology, you can now experience your favorite food without the extra calories. This air fryer can fry, bake, grill and roast with little to no oil.

Modern touch screen design: Sleek and modern look with advanced touch screen menu. New features include a start/stop button allowing you to change your program mid-cycle, as well as a built-in alarm function to remind you to shake your ingredients in 5, 10, and 15-minute increments.

8 preset cooking options & manual controls: Enjoy 8 pre-programmed cooking functions including fries/chips, pork, chicken, steak, shrimp, cake, fish and pizza. Or, use the manual controls to customize to your needs. This air fryer is equipped with a wide temperature range from 180F to 400F and a timer for up to 30 minutes.
Accessory kit included: Includes 8-inch baking pan, 8-inch pie/pizza pan, insert rack, insert rack W/ 3 skewers, toasting/warming rack, and silicone pot holder.
Recipe book included: Includes 50 recipes specifically made for GoWISE USA air fryers. Get started today with 50 step-by-step recipes to explore all that your new kitchen gadget has to offer.
Perfect Mother's day gift; Treat the Moms in your life to this family-sized air fryer that will make it easy to create healthier versions of her favorite fried foods in 30 minutes or less.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: A Kitchen Game-Changer Healthier and Easier Cooking Cook your favorite snacks or meals all in one appliance! The GoWISE USA Air Fryer uses Rapid Air Circulation Technology to circulate heat around ingredients making it possible to enjoy your snack or meal in 30 minutes or less! This 5.8-Quart model comes in a variety of colors, White, Black, Plum and Red making it the perfect addition to any kitchen! Large Touchscreen Display This air fryer features a large touchscreen display with a variety of settings, such as a Wide Temperature range of 180°F-400°F degrees, Cooking Timer up to 30 minutes, Start/Stop button to make it easier to change settings mid-cycle, Alarm Function to remind you to shake the contents in 5, 10, and 15 minute increments and 8 Presets: Fries/Chips, Pork, Chicken, Steak, Shrimp, Cake, Fish and Pizza The 8 built-in presets are designed with optimal times and temperatures to take the guesswork out of cooking! Detachable Non-Stick Basket and Pan Shake or transfer food to a serving plate easily with the detachable basket and pan. The detach button is equipped with a button guard to prevent accidental detachment. The detachable basket are coated with PFOA-free nonstick material to make cleaning up after meals quick and easy, so you can spend less time in the kitchen and more time with the ones you love. XL Accessory Set Transform your air fryer into an oven, grill, toaster, and more with the XL Accessory Set. The accessory set includes the following: Baking Pan (8 inches)Pizza Pan (8 inches)Multi-Purpose RackSkewer RackToasting RackSilicone Mat

Create Healthy & Delicious Meals in 30 Minutes or Less A Healthy Way to "Fry Indulge your cravings without the guilt! This air fryer allows you to fry your favorite foods without the extra calories by "frying" with air instead of dunking foods into oil! For an extra crunch, lightly spritz ingredients with healthier oils, such as olive oil, peanut oil, or sunflower oil! Grill, Roast, Toast All In One Expand the cooking possibilities of your air fryer by doing more than just frying. Grill juicy steaks, roast a pork loin, or even toast a slice of bread all in one versatile appliance. This air fryer has a 5.8-quart capacity making it ideal for households up to 4! Think Beyond the Fry Satisfy your sweet tooth and whip up a delicious cake, cookies, pies, turnovers and more. This air fryer gives you the option of using the "Cake" preset or setting a temperature as high as 400°F degrees. Bake to your heart's desire faster and easier without the hassle of using a traditional oven!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Not what I expected
reviews.reviewText: If you have space, its ok, quite large, maximum of 400 degrees whereas others go higher. Adjusting time is confusing, not as simple to operate as I would have liked. The capacity and additional accessories are a big plus. Must read the manual to enjoy. Overall ok. Flave to food a decent. Making Crunchy pork bits leave it to be desired. For the price, functions as expected. Not perfect but easy and great cooking.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 11, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I love this air fryer and it was a decent price! Worth every penny so far. It's been a year since I bought it and still works great!! The inserts are great too. Cooks food perfectly too. Never had an issue with it and would recommend!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 25, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I extensively researched the more spendy oven-like air fryers and hated that most seemed to smoke or break down after a year or less. I wanted to improve my cooking health and saw the reviews here and decided this price was acceptable if it broke after a year. I am extremely pleased with the results of this. I used to hate making fish. With this, spice your fish put it in and hit the button for fish. It doesn't matter if it's cod, salmon, or trout. They all come out crispy on the outside, juicy inside, and cooked perfectly! The same is said of chicken, whether a breast or a quarter piece. I just did a roast in this. Again amazed! In 30 minutes, I had a perfectly cooked medium-rare roast. Frozen tater tots, no oil, and cooked in 15 minutes! I love not taking 20 to 30 minutes to heat up the oven, plus the cooking time. I love this thing; it has positively changed my life.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 5, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Definitely would recommend.
reviews.reviewText: I have been looking for an air fryer for a while. A friend has this one and I just fell in love. It’s fairly easy to use. Lots of inserts. Not as easy to clean the inside as I thought, but I’m still getting use to it. The bucket however is easy to clean. I love the shape of the bucket. Not round, not square. Ost like a rectangle with rounded edges. Kind of a squared oval maybe. Hard to describe. But it’s perfect. I’ve made a handful of things in it so far, some way better than others but that’s my learning curve.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 27, 2022
reviews.reviewText: This was America's Test Kitchen 2nd place winner in their air fryer product test. I originally purchased their 1st place winner which was the Philips brand. Philips seemed to dry out the food too much for my liking. Returned the Philips and purchased this one. I have had it for 1year now, and I use it every day. In the past year I have only used my full size over twice. My very first air fryer was the NuWave brand, but it stopped working after 6 months, and was very hard to clean. This GoWise brand is much easier to clean, performs well, produces great quality food, pretty quiet operation, comes with a lot of great accessories, and is very nice looking. Although, I must say the material used in the Philips air fryer was by far the easiest one to clean. I have not needed to use many of the accessories that came with the unit. However, I have used the pizza pan about 5 times. The pizza pan has lost its coating over time even with me only hand washing it. I would still highly recommend this air fryer over other brands.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 12, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Highly recommend for first timers!
reviews.reviewText: I love this thing! It's super easy to use & clean - not to mention it cuts cooking time in half. I've never been able to make chicken as tender, juicy and with so much flavor before. There are TONS of air fryer recipes out there that I've finally been able to plan & make meals that even my picky kids will eat that are also so much healthier than using a deep fryer.I bought this as a first-time air fryer user, so I was solely dependent on reviews and didn't want to spend a ton on something I wasn't sure I was going to use. When I stumbled on this one, the price was great and was highly recommended.Since I haven't used any other air fryer and am still learning all of its features, I can only comment on this particular product but I will say as a family of 4, I do wish I got the bigger size since you can't overcrowd the pan in order to cook everything evenly. So, depending on the size of food & people you are cooking for, it may take several batches to complete. That being said, with the decease in cook time its usually not that big of a deal & the outcome is well worth the wait.So far, it's been perfect for us & highly recommend to those on the fence about purchasing one.

Purchased based on the positive reviews on America’s Test Kitchen. Very easy to use and clean. Large basket enables the user to air fry relatively large quantities of food at once, thereby reducing the number of multiple batches. For a family of four, it is perfect. We use ours regularly as a healthy alternative to frying and an energy efficient alternative to using the range.

He cocinado desde papas a la francesa hasta salmón y rib-eye de 1/4" y ha quedado excelente.Ayuda mucho los accesorios que tiene para poner ya sea 2 pisos de proteína o cocinar cosas diferentes como brocheta de camarón, etc.He hecho totopos también, quedan bien crujientes. No me arrepiendo de la compra a pesar que esta algo grande (tiene mucha capacidad).De la marca no tenia referencias, pero se ve buena la calidad de la freidora. reviews.reviewTitle: As close to fried without frying
reviews.reviewText: Pros: everything crispy on the outside and moist and juicy on the inside, cooks quickly, relatively quiet, easy to use, can use olive oil, way healthier than deep frying. Cons: takes up counter space, perforated non-stick basket takes a little more time to clean, does not replicate a professional deep fryer but as close as you can get.
